		<div id="comment_body_36401462">Seriously, who still gets spam email these days? Filtering solutions are fairly mature and effective. I might go so far as to say we're winning the battle... if it weren't for the fact that like 90% of all email is spam. Still, I publish my gmail address all over the feakin' place including usenet and I can't remember the last time I got a single piece of spam in my inbox or a missed email due to filtering. When I ran my own mail server I could filter out most spam as well using free tools and techiques. So</div>
